# Conventional Commits

All commits created or suggested in this repository **must** follow [Conventional Commits](https://www.conventionalcommits.org/).

## Subject line (required)

```
<type>(<scope>): <short description>
```

- **type** (pick one): `feat`, `fix`, `docs`, `style`, `refactor`, `perf`, `test`, `build`, `ci`, `chore`, `revert`
- **scope** (optional but preferred when obvious): area touched, e.g. `nvibe`, `plan`, `scribe`, `slides`, `deps`, `flight`
- **description**: imperative mood, lowercase start (after the colon), **no period** at the end; ~72 characters or less

## Examples

```text
feat(nvibe): add chat omit toggle for historical fences
fix(plan): handle empty model text in gemini response
docs(readme): document GEMINI_MODEL and scribe defaults
refactor(nvibe): extract coerce proposed app vue helper
chore(nvibe): refresh generated App.vue
```

## Breaking changes

If the change breaks consumers or APIs, add `!` after type/scope and explain in the body:

```text
feat(api)!: rename nvibe messages response field

BREAKING CHANGE: clients must use `lastNvibeTurn` instead of `turn`.
```

## Body and footer (optional)

Use a blank line after the subject, then bullet details or `BREAKING CHANGE:` / issue refs (`Closes #123`) as needed.

## Do not

- Vague subjects: `update`, `fix stuff`, `wip`, `changes`
- Non-conventional prefixes as the only line: `WIP`, `Misc`, `Address PR comments` without `type(scope):`

When squashing or amending, rewrite the result to satisfy this rule.
